Vice President Prof. Yemi Osinbajo has said Kogi has everything it requires to make it great if its resources are well harnessed with the right vision and leadership. Prof. Osinbajo, represented by the Director-General, Consumer Protection Council, Mr. Babatunde Irukera, said this at the “Unveiling of Kogi Vision” weekend in Abuja. He said Kogi is a state with diversity and confluence of opportunities, which are critical for the development of the state and the nation. He urged the state government to optimize the available resources to it, saying no matter how well the state was doing today, it was still not at the possible best it could be. The Founder of Kogi Vision, Dr. Tom Ohikere, said the project is a one-stop online platform that offers any information about the state, meant to assist government, investors and the people. Ohikere said the website, www.kogivision.org, launched by Prof. Osinbajo at the occasion, was a platform dedicated to the growth and development of the state. Governor Yahaya Bello, urged investors to invest in the state, saying lots of untapped opportunities are available in the Kogi. Governor Bello, represented by Senator Useni Yakubu (APC-Kogi Central), said his administration was tackling the issue of insecurity while embarking on infrastructural development that would take the state to greater heights. ‘Why Ebira should support Audu’ Youths rally support for Buhari, Osinbajo re-election in Kogi Osinbajo carries on campaign despite helicopter crash land Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin